This Lora can adjust the glossiness of the image.

V1.0 Setting it to a negative value will increase the glossiness and contrast of the image, making the overall image more vivid, especially the the pupils.

V1.0 Setting it to a positive value will reduce the glossiness and contrast of the image, making it softer and more realistic, and the pupils will also lose their luster.

Usage 1: Set to a negative value to increase the glossiness of the image, making the image more vivid and eye-catching;

Usage 2: Set to a positive value to make the image softer and more realistic. But in order to prevent the pupils from losing their luster, it is necessary to cooperate with the mask function of controlnet;

Usage 3: Intentionally creating a gloomy atmosphere. When set to a higher positive value, the color tone will darken and the character's pupils will completely lose their luster.

This is not to be used for anyone's commercial use. It will be taken down if it is used by someone to pass off as their own and profit off of it.

items.description:
BEFORE USING READ DESCRIPTION!

LoRA representing Gogalking artist's style, unable to totally mimic it but getting most of it. Big thanks to him for hard work.

V1.5 update:

Trigger word - gogalking.

Recommended weight is 0.7-0.79.

Higher weights can cause appearance of overfitting due to inability to train it perfectly.

Read preview images metadata if needed.

Mostly will give bad results at low resolution, quite good at normal highres portraits.

Can't do fangs as good as previous version, same goes for slit pupils.

V1.0 info:

Trigger word - gogalking.

Recommended weight - 1.

Learned concepts, can do relatively well in style of artist:

  • fangs, slit pupils, vampire, pointy ears, horns, facial expressions (such as embarrassed, blush, shocked)

Some times can make bright pupils, so add it to negatives if you dont want them to appear.

All preview images generated with highres fix, which is recommended for usage.

Not very flexible and usable with poses LoRAs, but can be utilized with characters LoRA quite good. Characters LoRA's compatibility preview.

Please, leave a review and comment what could be improved / fixed. Still not tested on realistic models.

===========================================================


MODEL UPDATE:

LoRA V1- (31/7/23)

-Update verse5 office by increasing number of dataset. This should improve the accuracy of her design.

Reference from Blue Archieve Character, Hanako. This model design to achieve multicostume with only short custom prompt.

Simplify about this Model:

-This Model quality has been train enough to work on weight 1.
-Quality Prompt such as "Masterpiece or Best Quality" is not necessary. This will hammered the quality of image been generated.

-User are expected to use Highres with denoise 0.1~0.3 incase some checkpoint shown degrading quality of image.

-This Model been train with DAdaptAdam.

-The Model had been train enough to represent each of it Trigger Word except "verse5 off1ce" due to lack of sample image, this may rectified by next version.
-The Halo may sometimes not appearing, user can input normal prompt "Halo" instead.

-The model may look desaturation due to Dadaptation optimizer, user are advise to use kl-f8-anime2 vae for clear saturation.

===========================================================

How to use Lora:
LoCon & LoHa (LyCoris):
-If user had update to latest SD1.5 or A1111, the Lora folder should supported Lycoris Model, otherwise user may still follow below instruction:
-Make sure your SD already contains LyCoris Extension https://github.com/KohakuBlueleaf/a1111-sd-webui-lycoris
-download the LoCon or LoHa models
-Move the data into your Stable Diffusion -> Models -> Lycoris

===========================================================

About Trigger Words:

-This Model came with 3 type trigger words for 5 different costume, "verse1 uniform", "verse2 swimsuit", "verse3 openshirt", "verse4 sport", "verse5 off1ce".

-optionally use normal prompt "Halo" incase you want her original aesthetic.
-do not use "Halo" prompt if there already Halo on generate image otherwise you be seeing 2 Halo colliding with each other.

-If user wish to change to their desire outfit prompt, trigger word are not necessary.
